# HTML semantics and accessibility

- Use landmarks: `header`, `nav`, `main`, `footer`; one `h1` per page; logical heading order.
- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a href="...">` for navigation; every `img` needs `alt` (empty `alt=""` only if decorative).
- Use `<form>` with associated `<label>` (or `aria-labelledby`) and appropriate `input` types.
- Include skip link to `#main-content` (or first landmark) and matching `id` on `main`.
- Set `lang` on `<html>` and viewport meta for responsive scaling.
- Prefer native HTML semantics over ARIA; add ARIA only when HTML cannot express the role/state (e.g. custom widgets).

```html
<!-- Avoid -->
<div onclick="...">Open</div>

<!-- Prefer -->
<button type="button">Open</button>
```
